    "air filter": "Air filter change is specified at the extended maintenance interval in Octavia III booklets (60,000 km is typical for petrol; diesels may differ).",
    "spark plugs": "Petrol TSI models specify spark plug replacement per the maintenance table—60,000 km is a common EU interval for four-cylinder engines.",
    "fuel filter": "TDI models require fuel filter replacement on the long-interval maintenance items; Škoda/VW diesel schedules commonly use 60,000 km—omit on pure petrol cars.",
    "DSG gearbox fluid": "Specialists recommend DSG fluid and filter around 60,000 km for long-term reliability of the dual-clutch unit.",
    "coolant flush": "Cooling system protection fades with age; exchange around 120,000 km is a sensible preventive step.",
    "brake fluid": "Škoda/VW Group specifies brake fluid replacement every 2 years on EU fixed-interval schedules, approximately every 60,000 km.",
    "check brake pads": "Brake pad inspection is part of the Škoda periodic maintenance programme at each major service."
